  <name>0cmake</name>
  <summary>0compile utility for CMake-based Ryppl projects</summary>
  <description>
0cmake can be used in a Ryppl project's 0install feed to build and install the
feed from source.  For example:

&lt;command name='compile'&gt; &lt;runner
interface='http://ryppl.github.com/feeds/ryppl/0cmake.xml'/&gt;
&lt;arg&gt;--component=bin&lt;/arg&gt; &lt;/runner&gt; &lt;/command&gt;</description>
  <category>Development</category>
  <category>Building</category>
  <homepage>http://github.com/ryppl/0cmake</homepage>
  <dc:author>Dave Abrahams &lt;dave@boostpro.com&gt;</dc:author>

  <group license="OSI Approved :: Boost Software License 1.0 (BSL-1.0)">
